headline: Spencer Jakab | ‘Free’ Stock Trading Is Expensive
summary: ? This is an online version of my Markets A.M. newsletter.  About half of all new U.S. brokerage accounts between 2016 and 2021 were opened at upstart Robinhood, which built its business around having no trading commissions.  When much larger competitors Schwab, TD Ameritrade, E*Trade and Fidelity finally followed suit, it was a scary moment.
